# CODEOWNERS
#
# Rules:
#   - Format: <path pattern>  <GitHub username or team>
#   - When a PR is created, GitHub automatically requests reviews from matching owners
#   - When used with Branch Protection "Require review from Code Owners",
#     these owners must approve before the PR can be merged
#   - Note: a file owner cannot review their own PRs
#
# In this project each task is owned end-to-end by one person; code ownership is not
# split by service. CODEOWNERS is used only to protect high-risk files such as
# requirement specs, task files, and workflow config.
# Before use: replace the placeholder usernames below with actual GitHub usernames.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Spec files (highest-priority — must be approved by tech-lead) ──────────────
.wiki/                          @tech-lead-username
WORKFLOW.md                     @tech-lead-username

# ── Task files (trackable by product owner / tech-lead) ───────────────────────
.tasks/                         @tech-lead-username

# ── GitHub config itself (prevent bypassing constraints) ──────────────────────
.github/                        @tech-lead-username
